  "texts": [
    "\"Power in operation is pragmatic, seeking and finding paths of least resistance and mobilizing the practical and conceptual resources that appear ready to hand\" [38].",
    "Critical approaches acknowledge this \"shape-shifting\" nature of power and similarly refuse to define precise antidotes to its influence.",
    "Rather, researchers must continually interrogate-based on their own positionality and research context-how systems of power may influence their data, their methods, and their results.For example, there are many studies for which it is entirely reasonable and appropriate to include a demographic analysis-examining behaviors by race, gender, or other personal characteristics.",
    "Yet, as we have seen, both race [17][18][19] and gender [4,20,21,45] are social constructs, shaped by systems of power.",
    "Any effort to classify people by race and gender will necessarily simplify what categories of race and gender are considered, and will likely misclassify some people into categories they wouldn't, or would prefer not to, self-select."
  ],
